The global Tay-Sachs disease treatment market is projected to witness significant growth by 2031, driven by increasing awareness about genetic disorders and advancements in medical research. The market is segmented based on type, treatment type, and end-user. Infantile Tay-Sachs disease, juvenile Tay-Sachs disease, and late-onset Tay-Sachs disease are the key types considered. Treatment types include enzyme replacement therapy, gene therapy, and symptomatic treatment. End-users of these treatments are hospitals, specialty clinics, and research institutes. The market is expected to expand as novel therapies and diagnostic tools become available, catering to the specific needs of patients with Tay-Sachs disease.

